M|systematic-debugging|Extracted debugging framework from `/Users/jesse/.claude/CLAUDE.md`:
M|systematic-debugging|- 4-phase systematic process (Investigation → Pattern Analysis → Hypothesis → Implementation)
M|systematic-debugging|- Core mandate: ALWAYS find root cause, NEVER fix symptoms
M|systematic-debugging|- Rules designed to resist time pressure and rationalization
M|systematic-debugging|**What to include:**
M|systematic-debugging|- Complete 4-phase framework with all rules
M|systematic-debugging|- Anti-shortcuts ("NEVER fix symptom", "STOP and re-analyze")
M|systematic-debugging|- Pressure-resistant language ("even if faster", "even if I seem in a hurry")
M|systematic-debugging|- Concrete steps for each phase
M|systematic-debugging|**What to leave out:**
M|systematic-debugging|- Project-specific ctx
M|systematic-debugging|- Repetitive variations of same rule
M|systematic-debugging|- Narrative explanations (condensed to principles)
M|systematic-debugging|1. **Rich when_to_use** - Included symptoms and anti-patterns
M|systematic-debugging|2. **Type: technique** - Concrete process with steps
M|systematic-debugging|3. **Keywords** - "root cause", "symptom", "workaround", "debugging", "investigation"
M|systematic-debugging|4. **Flowchart** - dec point for "fix failed" → re-analyze vs add more fixes
M|systematic-debugging|5. **Phase-by-phase breakdown** - Scannable checklist format
M|systematic-debugging|6. **Anti-patterns section** - What NOT to do (critical for this skill)
M|systematic-debugging|Framework designed to resist rationalization under pressure:
M|systematic-debugging|- "ALWAYS" / "NEVER" (not "should" / "try to")
M|systematic-debugging|- "even if faster" / "even if I seem in a hurry"
M|systematic-debugging|- "STOP and re-analyze" (explicit pause)
M|systematic-debugging|- "Don't skip past" (catches the actual behavior)
M|systematic-debugging|- **Phase 1 required** - Can't skip to implementation
M|systematic-debugging|- **Single hypothesis rule** - Forces thinking, prevents shotgun fixes
M|systematic-debugging|- **Explicit failure mode** - "IF your first fix doesn't work" with mandatory action
M|systematic-debugging|- **Anti-patterns section** - Shows exactly what shortcuts look like
M|systematic-debugging|- Root cause mandate in overview + when_to_use + Phase 1 + implementation rules
M|systematic-debugging|- "NEVER fix symptom" appears 4 times in different contexts
M|systematic-debugging|- Each phase has explicit "don't skip" guidance
